==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ekasilicon
<hw>Ek`a*sil"i*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.
<ets>⟦emac⟧ka</ets> one + E. <ets>silicon</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The name of a hypothetical element predicted by
<persfn>Mendeleev</persfn> and afterwards discovered and named
<altname>germanium</altname>; -- so called because it was a missing
analogue of the silicon group. See <er>Germanium</er>, and cf.
<er>Ekabor</er>. Also see <cref>periodic table</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eke</ent>⟦br⟧
